This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language generation from video content. It also involves event recognition, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper may involve machine learning techniques for object tracking and posture recognition, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper may involve information retrieval techniques for extracting relevant information from the video, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
